            <title>[LU-13318] lfs find returning obd_uuid: (null) failed No such device</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13318</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We&apos;re seeing the following errors when using &lt;tt&gt;lfs find&lt;/tt&gt; the following way:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[root@fir-rbh01 ~]# lfs find -m 1 -type f -C +1 /fir
obd_uuid: (null) failed No such device /fir/groups/slqi/augustine/db1/clusters/scop/cqid.00579431.hhr
obd_uuid: (null) failed No such device /fir/groups/slqi/augustine/db1/clusters/scop/cqid.00746150.hhr
obd_uuid: (null) failed No such device /fir/groups/slqi/augustine/db1/clusters/scop/cqid.00550309.hhr
obd_uuid: (null) failed No such device /fir/groups/slqi/augustine/db1/clusters/scop/cqid.00427996.hhr
obd_uuid: (null) failed No such device /fir/groups/slqi/augustine/db1/clusters/scop/cqid.00244859.hhr
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Although, we have not tested with 2.12.4 yet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That looks similar to this old issue: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1270&quot; title=&quot;lfs find -size returns &amp;quot;obd_uuid: (null) failed No such device&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1270&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1270&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
